
Citizens get a chance to speak out about planned changes on Memorial Drive, between I-285 and U.S. 78, at a Town Hall meeting Thursday at St. Timothy United Methodist Church in Stone Mountain. The 7 p.m. meeting at the church, 5365 Memorial Drive,  is hosted by State Reps Michele Henson and Karla Drenner, along with the civic organization PRISM (Pride Rings in Stone Mountain). Representatives from the Georgia Department of Transportation, the DeKalb County transportation and economic development departments, and Georgia Perimeter College also will attend the meeting to talk about the Memorial Drive Streetscape Project, as well as planned changes to the I-285/Memorial Drive intersection. 

